Interface ParticipantResponsibility<T extends PackageElement<T>>

  • All Superinterfaces:

    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Activity<T>, Artifact, ArtifactParticipantResponsibility, Choice, End, EntryPoint, ExitPoint, ExpansionInput, ExpansionOutput, Flow, FlowElement<T>, Fork, InputPin, Join, OutputPin, PseudoState, Service, Start
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActivityImpl, ArtifactImpl, ArtifactParticipantResponsibilityImpl, ChoiceImpl, EndImpl, EntryPointImpl, ExitPointImpl, ExpansionInputImpl, ExpansionOutputImpl, FlowElementImpl, FlowImpl, ForkImpl, InputPinImpl, JoinImpl, OutputPinImpl, ParticipantResponsibilityImpl, PseudoStateImpl, ServiceImpl, StartImpl
    public interface ParticipantResponsibility<T extends PackageElement<T>>
extends PackageElement<T>
    A representation of the model object 'Participant Responsibility'. Base class for elements for which participants can responsible for, accountable, consulted, or informed. See [Responsibility Assignment Matrix](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsibility_assignment_matrix) for more details.

    The following features are supported:

    • Responsible
    • Responsible Keys
    • Accountable
    • Accountable Keys
    • Consulted
    • Consulted Keys
    • Informed
    • Informed Keys
    See Also:
    FlowPackage.getParticipantResponsibility()

    • Method Detail

      • getResponsible

        EList<Participant> getResponsible()
        Returns the value of the 'Responsible' reference list. The list contents are of type Participant. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Responsible'. Participant(s) responsible for the element, e.g. for completion of an activity.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Responsible' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipantResponsibility_Responsible(), Participant.getResponsible()

      • getResponsibleKeys

        the value of the 'Responsible Keys' attribute list.

      • getAccountable

        EList<Participant> getAccountable()
        Returns the value of the 'Accountable' reference list. The list contents are of type Participant. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Accountable'. Participant(s) accountable for the element, i.e. ultimately answerable for the correct and thorough completion of an activity or artifact. Accountable must sign off (approve) work that _responsible_ provides.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Accountable' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipantResponsibility_Accountable(), Participant.getAccountable()
